item.description:
As the election draws near, we interview the remaining four parliamentary party leaders, in English, on the isuses that matter. <br/><br/> Hear clips from the final four party leader interviews Radio Sweden has done:
-Ulf Kristersson, leader of the Moderate party;
-Annie Lööf, leader of the Center party;
-Ebba Busch Thor, leader of the Christian Democrats;
-Isabella Lövin, co-spokesperson of the Green party.
We also hear from election officials as pre-election voting begins. An Islamist group urges Muslims in Sweden not to vote. How a new protest party in Gothenburg is causing panic among traditional parties. And the teenager skipping school in protest outside parliament.
Reporters: Nathalie Rothschild, Ulla Engberg, Dave Russell, Brett Ascarelli, Frank Radosevich.
Presented by Dave Russell

